text: Waik朝k朝 is a neighborhood of Honolulu, on the south shore of Oahu, Hawaii. Waikiki Beach is the shoreline in front of Waik朝k朝. The name means "spouting fresh water" in the Hawaiian language. This because the area had springs and streams that fed wetlands.Lloyd J. Soehren (2010). "lookup of waikiki". in Hawaiian Place Names. Ulukau, the Hawaiian Electronic Library.
